# Predicting 10-Year Coronary Heart Disease Risk Using Machine Learning

## Project Overview

Cardiovascular disease (CVD) remains the leading cause of death worldwide, accounting for approximately 17.9 million deaths each year according to the World Health Organization (WHO). Early identification of individuals at high risk for coronary heart disease (CHD) can enable preventative treatment strategies and lifestyle interventions before clinical symptoms develop.

The objective of this project is to develop and compare multiple supervised machine learning models for predicting the likelihood of developing coronary heart disease within ten years using demographic, behavioral, and clinical health information collected from the Framingham Heart Study dataset.

Three machine learning algorithms are implemented and evaluated:

- Linear Regression
- Logistic Regression
- K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)

Each model is trained using identical predictor variables and evaluated using multiple classification metrics to determine which algorithm provides the most accurate and clinically useful predictions.

---

# Project Objectives

The goals of this project are to:

- Perform exploratory data analysis (EDA)
- Investigate relationships among clinical variables
- Handle missing values appropriately
- Prepare the dataset for machine learning
- Compare multiple preprocessing strategies
- Train three predictive machine learning models
- Optimize KNN hyperparameters
- Evaluate each model using multiple performance metrics
- Identify influential risk factors associated with coronary heart disease
- Determine which model performs best overall

---

# Dataset

**Dataset**

Framingham Heart Study

Source:

https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/dileep070/heart-disease-prediction-using-logistic-regression

The Framingham Heart Study is one of the most influential longitudinal studies investigating cardiovascular disease risk. The dataset contains demographic, behavioral, and clinical variables used to predict whether an individual develops coronary heart disease within ten years.

---

# Target Variable

| Variable | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| TenYearCHD | Indicates whether the patient develops coronary heart disease within 10 years (0 = No, 1 = Yes) |

---

# Predictor Variables

### Demographic

- age
- male
- education

### Behavioral

- currentSmoker
- cigsPerDay

### Medical History

- BPMeds
- prevalentStroke
- prevalentHyp
- diabetes

### Clinical Measurements

- totChol
- sysBP
- diaBP
- BMI
- heartRate
- glucose

