# Data Preprocessing

The following preprocessing steps were performed:

- Duplicate observations removed
- Missing target values removed
- Continuous variables imputed using the median
- Binary variables imputed using the mode
- Dataset split into training and testing sets
- Stratified train-test split
- Standard scaling
- Min-Max scaling
- Processed datasets saved for model training

---

# Machine Learning Models

## Linear Regression

Although linear regression is intended for continuous outcomes, it is included as a baseline comparison model.

---

## Logistic Regression

Logistic regression predicts the probability of developing coronary heart disease using the logistic function and provides interpretable feature coefficients.

---

## K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)

KNN classifies patients according to the most common class among their nearest neighbors.

Hyperparameters optimized include:

- Number of neighbors
- Weighting method
- Distance metric

using GridSearchCV.

---

# Model Evaluation Metrics

Each model is evaluated using:

- Accuracy
- Precision
- Recall
- F1 Score
- ROC Curve
- ROC-AUC
- Confusion Matrix
- Mean Squared Error (Linear Regression)
- Mean Absolute Error (Linear Regression)
- R² Score (Linear Regression)

---

# Why ROC-AUC?

ROC-AUC measures a model's ability to distinguish between patients who will and will not develop coronary heart disease across all possible classification thresholds.

Higher ROC-AUC values indicate better discrimination between positive and negative cases.

---

# Feature Scaling

Two scaling methods are implemented.

## StandardScaler

Centers variables around zero with unit variance.

Used for:

- Logistic Regression
- KNN

---

## MinMaxScaler

Scales variables between 0 and 1.

Implemented for comparison purposes.

